olive oil
2 potatoes
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 packet beef mince
1 bag Soffritto Mix
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet garlic paste
½ sachet dried oregano
1 packet tomato paste
½ cup water
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with
boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat,
until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
Drain and return potato to the pan.
• Add the butter and milk to the potato, then
season with salt. Mash until smooth.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the
potato unpeeled.
Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help
mash the potatoes!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over high heat.
• Cook beef mince, breaking up with a spoon,
until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

TIP: For best results, drain excess oil from the pan
after cooking the mince.

• Add soffritto mix to the mince and cook until
softened, 4-5 minutes.

• Add baby spinach, garlic paste, dried oregano
and tomato paste and cook until fragrant and
wilted, 1 minute.
• Stir in the water, beef-style stock powder
and the brown sugar and cook until slightly
thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Season to taste.

• Preheat grill to medium-high.
• Transfer beef filling to a baking dish. Spread
mash over the top. Sprinkle over grated
Parmesan cheese.
• Grill pie until the mash is golden, 5-10 minutes.

TIP: Grills cook fast, so keep an eye on the pie!
Little cooks: Join in the fun by smoothing the mash
mixture evenly over the pie! Careful the filling is hot.

• Divide Italian beef and soffritto pie with mash
and Parmesan topping between plates. Enjoy!